Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of enabling robots to learn and execute collaborative manipulation plans from videos on the web. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) for object detection and tracking, machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) for learning representations of manipulation actions, and natural language processing (cs.CL) for generating human-interpretable robot commands. The focus on robotic manipulation suggests that the paper belongs to the robotics sub-category (cs.RO) of computer science.
